brary_support.json:6617:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.947368,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6622:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.947368,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6650:      \\\"analysis_markdown\\\": \\\"# Post-generation intervention report\\\\n\\\\nLibrary: org.apache.commons:commons-lang3:3.11\\\\nStage: metadata_fix_failed\\\\n\\\\n## Summary\\\\n\\\\nThe generated support failed in native test execution because `EventListenerSupportTest.serializationRoundTripDropsNonSerializableListenersAndRecreatesTransientFields()` hit a GraalVM native-image serialization/reflection limitation during `ObjectInputStream` deserialization.\\\\n\\\\n## Failure analysis\\\\n\\\\n### Failing test\\\\n\\\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/EventListenerSupportTest.java`\\\\n\\\\n### Root cause\\\\n\\\\nThis failure is **not a normal metadata gap** in the generated library support.\\\\n\\\\nThe Gradle failure shows `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()` from:\\\\n\\\\n- `java.io.ObjectStreamClass.newInstance(...)`\\\\n- `java.io.ObjectInputStream.readOrdinaryObject(...)`\\\\n\\\\nThe Codex metadata-fix log shows that it already tried the obvious metadata-based remedies:\\\\n\\\\n- adding reflection metadata for `java.lang.Object` default construction,\\\\n- marking the serialized test class for unsafe allocation,\\\\n- adding equivalent test-local metadata under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`.\\\\n\\\\nDespite that, the runtime still failed with the exact same `java.lang.Object()` error. That means this test is exercising a native-image/JDK deserialization path that is not resolved by the suggested metadata entry, rather than exposing unfinished commons-lang3 metadata.\\\\n\\\\n## Intervention\\\\n\\\\nRemoved the unsupported generated test:\\\\n\\\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.11/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/EventListenerSupportTest.java`\\\\n\\\\nNo metadata files were modified as part of this intervention.\\\\n\\\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\\\n\\\\nThe failure was isolated to one serialization round-trip scenario. The native test report shows the rest of the generated commons-lang3 support working: 52 other tests passed, including coverage for reflection-heavy APIs such as:\\\\n\\\\n- `AnnotationUtils`\\\\n- `ClassUtils`\\\\n- `ConstructorUtils`\\\\n- `EqualsBuilder`\\\\n- `FieldUtils`\\\\n- `HashCodeBuilder`\\\\n- `MethodUtils`\\\\n- `ReflectionToStringBuilder`\\\\n- `SerializationUtils`\\\\n- `TypeUtils`\\\\n\\\\nThat passing coverage indicates the generated metadata and tests still provide meaningful support for `org.apache.commons:commons-lang3:3.11`. Only the `EventListenerSupport` serialization test should be dropped because it depends on a native-image deserialization behavior that Codex could not fix through metadata registration.\\\"\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6661:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 8.73\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6682:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6687:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6692:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/sc