ly invokes `ClassLoader#defineClass(...)` at runtime for `GeneratedAnnotationBuilderCoverage...`.\\\\n\\\\nThe native run failed with `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.UnsupportedFeatureError: Classes cannot be defined at runtime by default when using ahead-of-time Native Image compilation`.\\\\n\\\\nThat is not a missing-registration error and not a missing metadata problem. The failure is caused by runtime class definition being unsupported by default in Native Image.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `AnnotationBuilderTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 2. `DefaultClassFactoryTest.invokesMethodInvokeLineUsingSyntheticDefaultClassFactoryWithoutProtectionDomain()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: non-metadata JDK/platform incompatibility.\\\\n\\\\nThis test initializes `org.jboss.classfilewriter.DefaultClassFactory`, whose implementation reflectively looks up the internal field `AccessibleObject.override`. On this GraalVM/JDK 25 environment, that field is not present, so initialization fails with a synthesized `NoSuchFieldException: override`.\\\\n\\\\nThis is not a reachability metadata issue. Metadata cannot restore a removed or unavailable JDK internal field.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 3. `DefaultClassFactoryTest.definesClassThroughDefaultFactoryUsingProvidedClassLoaderAndProtectionDomain()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: same non-metadata JDK/platform incompatibility as above.\\\\n\\\\nThis test is also blocked by `DefaultClassFactory` initialization against the missing `override` field. The assertion mismatch in the failure excerpt is downstream from that initialization problem and does not indicate missing metadata.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 4. `DefaultClassFactoryTest.invokesMethodInvokeLineUsingSyntheticDefaultClassFactoryWithProtectionDomain()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: same non-metadata JDK/platform incompatibility as above.\\\\n\\\\nBecause `DefaultClassFactory` cannot initialize successfully, the test fails with `NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class org.jboss.classfilewriter.DefaultClassFactory`.\\\\n\\\\nAgain, this is not a metadata gap; it is a consequence of the unavailable JDK internal field relied on by the library code path.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\\\n\\\\nThe remaining generated support is still useful and should be kept because it exercises library behavior that does work under Native Image once the generated metadata is present.\\\\n\\\\nThe surviving tests still cover:\\\\n\\\\n- class structure and bytecode generation\\\\n- switch generation and exception-handler bytecode\\\\n- runtime-visible annotation writing for class, field, method, and parameter targets\\\\n- generic signatures and checked exceptions\\\\n- `CodeAttribute` frame merging using loaded concrete collection types\\\\n\\\\nThose tests all passed after removing the unrelated native-image/JDK-internal cases, so the generated support is not scaffold-only and should not be discarded just because a few tests targeted unsupported runtime class-definition behavior.\\\\n\\\\n## Metadata status\\\\n\\\\nNo additional metadata-only failure remained in the provided failure set.\\\\n\\\\nThe Codex log indicates the metadata fix progressed far enough to resolve the metadata-driven failures that were actually fixable here. The remaining failing tests were blocked by:\\\\n\\\\n- Native Image runtime class-definition restrictions\\\\n- reliance on the missing JDK internal field `override`\\\\n\\\\nBecause those are not metadata issues, the correct intervention was to remove the generated tests that depended on those unsupported behaviors rather than remove the rest of the generated support or attempt further metadata edits.\\\"\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9566:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 34.74\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9586:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9600:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 100.0\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9621:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9626:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9660:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 7.16\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9683:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 24.87\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9704:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.9375,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9709:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.666667,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9714:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.914286,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9742:      \\\"analysis_markdown\\\": \\\"# Post-generation intervention report\\\\n\\\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\\\n\\\\n## Summary\\\\n\\\\nThe native image built successfully, and the remaining failures were two native-runtime behavioral assertions rather than missing reachability metadata. There was no `Missing*RegistrationError` in the Gradle failure output. The generated support should therefore be kept, but the two unsupported native-only tests were removed.\\\\n\\\\nI also confirmed that the generated test suite passes on the JVM and that `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA --stacktrace` passes after removing the two failing native-only tests.\\\\n\\\\n## Failure analysis\\\\n\\\\n### 1. `org.jboss.logmanager.LogManagerTest > readConfigurationFallsBackToLogManagerClassLoaderWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsConfigurator()`\\\\n\\\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\\\n- **Why:** `LogManager.construct(...)` uses `Class.forName(name, true, contextClassLoader)` first and then falls back to the `LogManager` class loader. In the native image, the assertion `rejectingClassLoader.rejectedClassLoadAttempted` stayed `false`, even though the configurator was still instantiated successfully.\\\\n- **Interpretation:** this test depends on observing a custom `ClassLoader.loadClass(...)` rejection path for an image-contained class. That is a native-image class-loading behavior difference, not missing metadata. If metadata were missing, the failure would have been a registration error or reflective instantiation failure, not a plain `assertThat(...).isTrue()` failure.\\\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and its test-only helpers from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/LogManagerTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 2. `org.jboss.logmanager.formatters.Formatters12Test > extendedExceptionFormattingUsesClassLoadingFallbacksAndClassResourceLookup()`\\\\n\\\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\\\n- **Why:** the native failure was again a boolean assertion (`loadedFromBytes`, `rejectedSystemTargetAttempted`, or `classResourceRequested`) staying `false`, not a missing registration error. This test tries to verify that `%E` formatting forces a custom context class loader to byte-define a target class and then performs `.class` resource lookup through that loader.\\\\n- **Interpretation:** the formatter output path is preserved, but the test relies on runtime-observable custom class loading and resource lookup behavior that native image does not preserve in the same way for image-contained classes. The native image already built successfully, so this is not evidence of missing metadata.\\\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and the test-only helper loader/classes that existed solely for it from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/formatters/Formatters12Test.java`.\\\\n\\\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\\\n\\\\nThe remaining generated support still exercises meaningful `jboss-logmanager` behavior that is relevant to reachability metadata:\\\\n\\\\n- context-class-loader-based configurator and locator instantiation still has coverage\\\\n- bootstrap fallback for exception formatting still has coverage\\\\n- privileged exception class resource lookup still has coverage\\\\n- property-based handler/filter/formatter/error-manager configuration still has coverage\\\\n- serialization-related coverage for the map implementations still has coverage\\\\n- default configuration lookup and typed array handling still have coverage\\\\n\\\\nIn short, only the two tests that depended on native-image-incompatible custom class-loading observability were removed. The rest of the generated suite still validates real library behavior and should be preserved.\\\"\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9753:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 26.16\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9774:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.9375,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9779:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9784:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.942857,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9812:      \\\"analysis_markdown\\\": \\\"# Post-generation intervention report\\\\n\\\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\\\n\\\\n## Summary\\\\n\\\\nThe post-generation failures had two different causes:\\\\n\\\\n1. `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()` in the Codex metadata-fix log was **metadata-related**.\\\\n2. `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` in the final Gradle failure was **not metadata-related**; it depended on JVM class-loader fallback behavior that does not hold under Native Image.\\\\n\\\\nI removed the generated `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` test and kept the rest of the generated support.\\\\n\\\\n## Failure analysis\\\\n\\\\n### 1. Codex log failure: metadata-related\\\\n\\\\nThe Codex log shows a `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` from:\\\\n\\\\n- `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()`\\\\n\\\\nMissing entry reported by Native Image:\\\\n\\\\n- `java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock$Sync.readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream)`\\\\n\\\\nThat failure came from Java deserialization of `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap`, so it was a real reachability-metadata gap rather than a bad test. This support should be preserved because it covers an actual native-image requirement for the library's serialization path.\\\\n\\\\n### 2. Remaining Gradle failure: not metadata-related\\\\n\\\\nThe remaining failing test was:\\\\n\\\\n- `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()`\\\\n\\\\nThis failed on:\\\\n\\\\n- `assertThat(rejectingClassLoader.wasRejected()).isTrue()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause:\\\\n\\\\n- The test assumes the formatter will first try to resolve the stack-frame class through the thread context class loader, observe a `ClassNotFoundException`, and only then fall back to the caller loader.\\\\n- In Native Image, class resolution for already-linked image classes does not preserve that JVM class-loading interaction in the same way. The formatted stack trace is still produced, but the custom rejecting loader is never asked to load the class, so `wasRejected()` stays `false`.\\\\n- No `Missing*RegistrationError` was reported for this failure, so this was not a metadata problem.\\\\n\\\\nThis is therefore a Native Image class-loading/runtime-semantics issue in the generated test, and removing that generated test was the correct intervention.\\\\n\\\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\\\n\\\\nThe rest of the generated support still exercises real library behavior and should remain in place:\\\\n\\\\n- serialization coverage for `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap` and `FastCopyHashMap`\\\\n- resource lookup coverage for `DefaultConfigurationLocator`\\\\n- formatter/resource coverage in `Formatters12Test`\\\\n- configuration loading and component instantiation coverage in `LogManagerTest` and `PropertyConfiguratorTest`\\\\n\\\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata-related formatter fallback test, the coordinate passed again with:\\\\n\\\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\\\n- `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\\\n\\\\nSo the generated metadata-backed support is still valuable and should be kept; only the unsupported caller-loader fallback assertion needed to be dropped.\\\"\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9823:      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 26.04\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9844:            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9849:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9877:      \\\"analysis_markdown\\\": \\\"# Post-generation intervention report\\\\n\\\\nLibrary: org.jboss.narayana.jta:jta:5.12.4.Final\\\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\\\n\\\\n## Summary\\\\n\\\\nThe native test failures were metadata-related, not caused by an unsupported Narayana feature, a test bug, or a platform limitation that would justify deleting generated tests.\\\\n\\\\nThe Codex log shows that the generated support was incomplete during the metadata-fix loop. In particular, the two serialization-focused tests needed test-only serialization metadata, and removing them would have thrown away valid coverage for real native-image requirements.\\\\n\\\\n## Failure-by-failure root cause\\\\n\\\\n### `JNDIManagerTest.bindTransactionSynchronizationRegistryImplementationUsesConfiguredClass()`\\\\n\\\\n- The Gradle failure excerpt showed reflective instantiation of `com.arjuna.ats.jta.common.JTAEnvironmentBean` failing through `BeanPopul